Description. Size: 0.75–1.05 mm females ( holotype 0.88 mm). Colour: blue greyish; pigment more concentrated in eye fields. Body long and slender (
Fig 1–2
). Dorsal chaetae smooth and pointed. SA macrochaeta on Abd IV 0.30–0.35, on Abd V 0.45–0.50 times the tergite length (
Fig 6
).

Five omma on each side of head. PAO long and narrow, 4.5–5.5 times as long as an omma, with two posterior chaetae (
Fig 9
). 2 /5,5,4 labral chaetae. Maxillary palp bifurcate with three sublobal hairs.
